<div><h3>MSEA 3130 - Sports Finance </h3>  <p><hr>This course provides an analysis of the multi-billion-dollar sports industry and the various revenues and expenses associated with operating a sport business.  Proper budgeting, forecasting and financial planning are critical steps to ensure effective fiscal decision-making.  This course takes a practical approach to explain how revenue is obtained and how it is spent effectively to foster growth for the sport organization.   <br><br><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> <a href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=29&coid=105248" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=29&coid=105248&print', '3', 770, 530, 'yes');return false;" rel="remote /ajax/preview_course.php?catoid=29&coid=105248&display_options[location]=tooltip&show" id="tt6097" target="_blank">MSEA 3000 Introduction to the Sports Industry</a><span style="display: none !important">&#160;</span> </p>

